         <div><p style="indent">
            Whereas, <choice><orig>It</orig><reg>it</reg></choice> seems to be the custom<lb/>
            prevailing in the other larger cities<lb/>
            of <name type="place">Florida</name> and the more pop<lb break="no"/>ulous cities of the South to designate their<lb/>
            public schools by names instead<lb/>
            of numbers; and
         </p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            Whereas, <choice><orig>We</orig><reg>we</reg></choice> share the com<lb break="no"/>mon desire with other citizens to<lb/>
            all <name type="person">Jacksonville</name> maintain its<lb/>
            place in the front lines with<lb/>
            other cities in the march of prgress; therefore,
         </p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            Resolved, <choice><orig>That</orig><reg>that</reg></choice> we approve<lb/>
            the suggestion of <name type="person">Miss Eartha M. M. White</name><lb/>
            on the future designations of<lb/>
            the colored public schools in the city of<lb/>
            <name type="place">Jacksonville</name> as follows:
         </p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            <name type="place">Oakland Graded School</name> to be<lb/>
            -- etc.
         </p></div>
         <div><p>
            Respectfully submitted,<lb/>
            __________<lb/>
            __________}Committee<lb/>
            __________
         </p></div>
         <pb n="4" facs= "../images/ew_f5_1697_004.jpg"/>   
         <div><p><choice><orig>1</orig><reg></reg></choice></p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            Whereas, <choice><orig>We</orig><reg>we</reg></choice> have been<lb/>
            Whereas, We have been<lb/>            
            approached by <name type="person">Miss Eartha M. M.<lb/>  
            White</name> suggesting the advisability<lb/> 
            of designating our colored<lb/> 
            public schools in <name type="place" subtype="city">Jacksonville</name><lb/> 
            by more significant and ap<lb break="no"/>pealing names; and  
         </p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            Whereas, <choice><orig>We</orig><reg>we</reg></choice> feel, too, that<lb/> 
            some bit of history should<lb/>
            be associated with the name<lb/>
            of each school as a matter of<lb/>
            sentiment so well as inspiration;<lb/> 
            therefore,                                   
         </p></div>
         <div><p style="indent">
            Resolved, That we hereby <add type="caret">humbl<supplied reason="writer apparently ran out of space">y</supplied></add>
            petition our <name type="organization">Honorable Board<lb/>            
            of Public Instruction</name> to grant with<lb/> 
            us the following changes in the<lb/>
            names of our colored public<lb/>  
            schools in this county:
         </p></div>
            <div><p>
            <name type="place">Oakland Graded School</name> to be<lb/>
            known as, etc.</p></div> 
